<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{hazu}}</strong> which indicates the speaker's belief that something will happen (or happened).
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<strong>@HI{{hazu}}</strong> indicates an expectation based on some reliable knowledge and so it is more than just a guess.
<p></p>

An expectation that something will not be the case can be expressed either by negating the sentence before <strong>@HI{{hazu}}</strong>
or by following  the sentence with <strong>@HI{{hazu}}</strong> @HI{{ha/ga nai}}. The latter construction carries heavier weight.
<p></p>

<strong>@HI{{hazu}}</strong> behaves as a noun so if "S <strong>@HI{{hazu}}</strong>" is a relative clause, @HI{{no}} follows it.
<p></p>

